claim.claim-text:
The method of claims 2 or 3, wherein providing the graphical feedback information comprises one or more of:
displaying an arrow pointing to the selected page indicator;
changing a shape of the selected page indicator;
changing a color of the selected page indicator;
changing a size of the selected page indicator;
displaying a title associated with the selected page indicator; and
replacing the selected page indicator with the selected icon.

The method of any one of claims 1 to 9, further comprising:
detecting an initiation of a second icon move of a second selected icon;
moving the second selected icon to a second selected page;
receiving an indication to return the GUI to a normal interaction mode; and
placing the GUI in the normal mode from the rearrangement mode.

1. A method of rearranging icons (110, 120, 126) between a plurality of pages (114, 116, 122, 134) of a graphical user interface (GUI), each page associated with a respective page indicator (112) displayed in the GUI, the GUI displaying a single page at a time, the method comprising:
detecting (2002) an initiation of an icon move of a selected icon (126b) displayed on a current page (122);
determining (2004) a selected page indicator (122d) of the plurality of page indicators (122) based on a proximity of a page selection input (128c);
providing a graphical feedback information highlighting the selected page indicator of the plurality of page indicators;
determining if a page (134) associated with the selected page indicator provides sufficient space for the selected icon to be moved to wherein if there is not sufficient space on the page the graphical feedback information is further modified; and
moving (2006) the selected icon (126b) to the page (134) associated with the selected page indicator (122d).

2. The method of claim 1, wherein providing the graphical feedback information comprises one or more of:
displaying an arrow pointing to the selected page indicator;
changing a shape of the selected page indicator;
changing a color of the selected page indicator;
changing a size of the selected page indicator;
displaying a title associated with the selected page indicator; and
replacing the selected page indicator with the selected icon.

8. The method of any one of claims 1 to 7, further comprising:
detecting an initiation of a second icon move of a second selected icon;
moving the second selected icon to a second selected page;
receiving an indication to return the GUI to a normal interaction mode; and
placing the GUI in the normal mode from the rearrangement mode.
